description.narrative: The overall project development objective is to facilitate the expansion of electricity supply of hydro-power in Pakistan. The Project would also improve access to socio-economic services for local communities in the project area and build WAPDA’s capacity to prepare future hydropower projects. This would be achieved by installing a 2,160 MW hydropower plant on the main Indus River, which can be expanded to 4,320 MW in future at very low cost. The Project is a “high-risk-high reward” operation aimed at providing low cost non-carbon renewable energy.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Annual Work Plans: PA (W) and PA(N), Schedule, Sec I.D | Description :WAPDA and NTDC will prepare annual workplans and budgets for each year of project implementation by October 31 of each year | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Capacity Building Activities: PA(W), Schedule, Sec I.E.4 | Description :WAPDA to ensure that TORs forconsultants services for capacity building activities under sub-components G.2 and G.3 (engineering, operation and maintenance ofdams and strategic studies for pilots and future investments), shall comply with the Bank’s environmental and safeguard policystandards. TORs to be cleared with the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Compliance: PA(W), Schedule, Sec I.E.2 & I.E.3;PA(N), Sch, Sec I.E.3 & I.E.4 | Description :WAPDA and NTDC toensure, prior to commencing any civil works: (i) all necessary governmental permits and clearances; (ii) compliance with allpre-constructions requirements; (iii) resettlement of affected person and prior and full payment of compensation; and (iv)obligation of contractor to comply with the applicable safeguard documents. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Designs of transmission line and EARF and LARF: | Description :GoP would ensure that NTDC would develop designsof the transmission line according to acceptable international standards and prepare and implement an EMP and Resettlement ActionPlan (RAP), according to the agreed Environmental Assessment and Review Framework (EARF) and Land Acquisition ResettlementFramework (LARF) prior to inviting bid or undertaking preparatory works for respective activities | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :EMP and SRMP: Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I.D.1 | Description :GoP would ensure that WAPDA willimplement the agreed Environmental Management Plan (EMP) and Social and Resettlement Management Plan (SRMP) and these plans wouldbe updated time to time as agreed by the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :EPP and O&MP: PA (W), Schedule, Sec I.E.7 | Description :WAPDA to prepare detailed Emergency Preparedness Plan(EPP) and O&M Plan (OMP) for the operation of DHP prior to the impoundment ofthe reservoir, twelve months prior to impoundment forthe EPP and six months for the OMP. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :ESU: Project Agreement (W), Schedule, Section 1.A.2 | Description :WAPDA would ensure that the environmental andsocial unit of the PMU is fully staffed and its work plan is finalized within three months of the effectiveness, thereafter,throughout the project period | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Escrow Account: Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Sec II.B.4 | Description :GoP to cause NTDC (or the entityacting as Central Power Purchase Agency) to maintain the Escrow Account opened under Tarbela IV with a balance of reservesequivalent to a period of billing by WAPDA to said entity (not to exceed two months). GoP will ensure the availability of fundsfor the capitalization of that Escrow Account, throughout project period and thereafter. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :GAAP: Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I.C | Description :GoP to ensure that WAPDA and NTDC implementthe Project in accordance with the Governance and Accountability Action Plan (GAAP) | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Grievance Redress Committee: PA (W) & (N), Schedule, Sec I.E.6 (b) | Description :WAPDA and NTDC wouldestablish and maintain on-site a Grievance Redress Committees (GRCs) throughout the Project implementation period with TORs andcomposition satisfactory to the Bank, one and six months after effectiveness for WAPDA and NTDC respectively. | Frequency:CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :List of displaced persons: PA (W) & (N), Schedule, Sec I.E.6 (a) | Description :WADPA and NTDC to maintain intheir websites an updated list of displaced persons on account of Project implementation, publicly disclosing their identities andthe compensation entitlements and amounts paid to them. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :NTDC: PA (N), Schedule, Sec I.A.1(a) and Sec I.A.2 | Description :National Transmission and Despatch Company(NTDC) would maintain its PMU with terms of reference, composition and staffing acceptable to the Bank. NTDC shall minimize oravoid the turn-over of staff and consultants | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :PMU: PA (W), Schedule, Sec I.A.1 (a), (b) & (c) and Sec I.A.3 | Description :Water and Power DevelopmentAuthority (WAPDA) will maintain the Project Management Unit (PMU), an independent panel of experts (IPOE), and constructionsupervision consultants (CSCs), with terms of reference (TORs), composition, staffing and qualification acceptable to the Bank.WAPDA shall minimize or avoid the turn-over of staff and consultants | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Management and Monitoring: PA (W), Schedule, Sec I.A.1 (d) | Description :WAPDA will engage andthereafter maintain, project management, monitoring and evaluation consultants, under TORs and contractual arrangementssatisfactory to the Bank, within six months after effectiveness (then throughout Project implementation) | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Steering Committee: Financing Agreement Schedule 2, Sec I.A.2 | Description :Government of Pakistan tomaintain a Project Steering Committee with composition satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project design and construction supervision: PA (N), Schedule, Sec I.A.1 (b) | Description :NTDC will engage andthereafter maintain, project design and construction supervision consultants, under TORs and contractual arrangements satisfactoryto the Bank, within six months after effectiveness (then throughout Project implementation) | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Thresholds for payments out of IDA: Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Sec IV.B.2 | Description :Payments ofUSD50,000 or more out of IDA financing for land acquisition, compensation of properties and resettlement and rehabilitation will:(a) require the Bank’s prior review and approval; (b) have an overall ceiling of USD111 million equivalent; and (c) be eligible forfinancing if made within 36 months as of the effectiveness of the credit. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
The Borrower shall maintain the PSC and the Project Implementing Entity shall maintain the PMU.

The Borrower, NDTC, and WAPDA shall ensure project implementation with appropriate health, safety, social, and environmentalstandards and practices, in accordance with Safeguards Instruments. In addition to standard provisions: strengthening of OHScapacity; compliance and monitoring; support and monitoring of OHS at contractors’ level; and periodic audits by reputable expertsstarting 9/30/2021.
The Borrower, WAPDA and the Project Implementing Entity shall participate in the Mid-term Review.
The Borrower, the Project Implementing Entity and WAPDA shall apply throughout the period of implementation of the Project safetymeasure to safeguard the communities in accordance with the ESMP.
The Project Implementing Entity shall prepare, submit to the Bank for approval and comply with Annual Work Plans and Budgets.
